  <div class="page">
    <p>Concluding Remarks</p>
    <p>We designed and implemented ipShield which - proposes the use of inferences as the currency for privacy and utility</p>
    <p>specification. - advocates that the burden of configuring fine-grained privacy rules</p>
    <p>should be shifted from the user to the system. - provides insight into how and what data is being used by apps and better</p>
    <p>visibility into potential risks and consequences of sharing data.</p>
    <p>Going forward we want to... - develop the rule recommender to generate rules for obfuscating data. - augment ipShield with ability to perform static analysis of app code to</p>
    <p>better understand the risks presented by the apps. - allow crowd-sourcing for bootstrapping of rules.</p>
    <p>ipShield can be downloaded at http://tinyurl.com/ipshieldgit</p>
  </div>
